attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the GoPro to change the battery. Inspects the GoPro to find the battery door, as he cant find it the instructor tells him how to find it and open it. The student finds the battery door but cant open it so the instructor continues to explain how to open it. The student accidentally turns on the GoPro and the instructor asks the student to turn it back off so the student turns off the GoPro. The instructor continues to explain how to open the battery door and finally opens it. The student pulls on the battery and removes it. Then he grabs the new battery, inserts it on the GoPro and closes de battery door. Next, the student starts looking for the place to change the SD card and again the instructor tells him where to find it. The student opens the battery door again, but accidentally detaches it. The instructor asks the student to reattach the battery door and the student reattaches it. Then the student removes the battery and tries to remove the old SD card, the instructor tells the students to push or click on the SD card to reject it. The student removes the SD card, inserts the new sd card and the battery and closes the battery door.Next, the student turns on the GoPro and then turns it off.Next, the student grabs the strap, tries to assemble it to the GoPro but hes unable to do it so the instructor ask the student to open the mount at the bottom of the GoPro. The student opens the mount and attaches the GoPro to the strap screwing them together. Then the student removes the GoPro from the strap, attaches it to the tripod and screws them together. Then the student detaches the GoPro from the Tripod and attaches it to the handheld grip but struggles to insert them together, having to reset a few times. Finally the student removes the GoPro from the handheld grip and leaves all the pieces on the table.
